MAN Plans to Start Production at Site in St. Petersburg, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-04-11T01:33:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/man-plans-to-start-production-at-site-in-st-petersburg-ft-says.html
MAN SE is planning to open a
factory in  St. Petersburg ,  Russia , the Financial Times reported,
citing two people close to the situation.  Chief Executive Officer Georg Pachta-Reyhofen is to sign an
investment agreement with the governor of St Petersburg on April
14, the people said, according to the FT. The plant will include
a complete assembly site and will allow use of an existing
facility to enable the company to start production immediately,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 